Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.68,0:02:15.69,1080P-sgsm-50,,0,0,0,,洛希极限(Rochelimit)是一个天体对自身的引力与第二个天体\N对它造成的潮汐力相等时两个天体的距离。当两个天体的距离\N少于洛希极限，天体就会倾向碎散，继而成为第二个天体的行星环。\N它以首位于1848计算这个极限的法国天文学家爱德华·洛希命名。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.04,0:03:56.31,1080P-sgsm-50,,0,0,0,,木卫一 艾奥(Io) 是木星的四颗伽利略卫星中最靠近木星的一颗卫星，\N其直径为3,642公里，是太阳系第四大卫星。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.66,0:04:33.52,1080P-sgsm-50,,0,0,0,,Scott这里有问题 RL-10的比冲应该都在400s以上\N要用于火神火箭的最新版本RL10C-1-1 比冲为453.8 s
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.29,0:00:05.63,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Hello it's Scott Manley here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.29,0:00:05.63,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,你好 我是Scott Manley
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.92,0:00:09.91,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,This week a movie trailer appeared which well I really want to talk about.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.92,0:00:09.91,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,本周发布了一个电影预告片 我真的想谈谈它
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.00,0:00:11.50,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Not because I think it's a good movie
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.00,0:00:11.50,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,不是因为我认为它是一部好电影
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.56,0:00:14.22,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,but because it poses an interesting question.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.56,0:00:14.22,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而是因为它提出了一个有趣的问题
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.58,0:00:16.41,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,The movie is moonfall
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.58,0:00:16.41,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这部电影是《月球坠落》
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.42,0:00:22.18,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and it features a moon sliding just across the surface of the earth as if it were in low earth orbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.42,0:00:22.18,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,并且它的重头戏是 月亮在地球表面滑动 就像它在低地球轨道上一样
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.22,0:00:25.92,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,So I wanted to basically show what it would take to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.22,0:00:25.92,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,因此 我想基本上展示出要做到这一点需要什么
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.24,0:00:29.17,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And of course mock the movie a little as we're doing at.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.24,0:00:29.17,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,当然 在我们做这些的同时 也会对电影进行一些模拟
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.18,0:00:32.02,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,So this is a system called universe sandbox.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.18,0:00:32.02,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,所以现在展示的 是一个叫做宇宙沙盒的系统
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.07,0:00:36.02,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,It's basically a gamified simulation of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.07,0:00:36.02,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它基本上是一个游戏化的宇宙模拟
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.03,0:00:38.67,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and you can load up a simulation of the solar system
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.03,0:00:38.67,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,并且 你可以加载一个太阳系的模拟
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.04,0:00:43.87,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and we can select the moon and we can go into its motion and adjust its velocity
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.04,0:00:43.87,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而我们可以选择月球 并且我们可以设置它的运动 调整它的速度
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.90,0:00:45.05,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,so that's what we're going to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.90,0:00:45.05,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,所以这就是我们将要做的
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.38,0:00:49.62,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Now we want to bring it down so that it passes just above the surface of the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.38,0:00:49.62,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,那么 我们想把它降下来 使它刚好经过地球表面
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.67,0:00:52.80,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,We want to get its pericenter distance to about 9000.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.67,0:00:52.80,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,我们想让它的近心点距离达到约9000
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.01,0:00:57.20,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,That means if you add the radius of the moon in the earth they do not collide.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.01,0:00:57.20,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这意味着如果你把月球和地球的半径加在一起 它们不会相撞
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.50,0:00:58.79,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,So I'm going to drag this down.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.50,0:00:58.79,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,所以我打算把这个拖下来
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.82,0:01:02.01,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Now the initial speed is about one kilometer per second.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.82,0:01:02.01,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,现在的初速度大约是每秒1公里
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.48,0:01:06.79,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,We're probably going to have to drop it down to about 200 meters per second
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.48,0:01:06.79,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,我们可能要把它降到每秒200米左右
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.82,0:01:09.50,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,to get our velocity low enough that
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.82,0:01:09.50,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,才能使我们的速度足够低
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.52,0:01:16.19,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,it just skims over the surface of the earth for a maximum cinematic dramatic effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.52,0:01:16.19,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,使月球只是在地球表面滑过 以获得最大的电影戏剧效果
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.72,0:01:19.30,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Now the simulation is running in real time right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.72,0:01:19.30,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,现在 这个模拟正在实时运行
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.31,0:01:21.61,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,In fact it's running with today's date.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.31,0:01:21.61,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,事实上 它是以今天的日期运行的
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.98,0:01:24.86,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,But I can click this to run the thing faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.98,0:01:24.86,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但我可以点击这个来加速运行
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.10,0:01:28.63,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,I have to remember however to slow it down once we get close.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.10,0:01:28.63,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,然而 我必须记住 一旦它们开始接近时 就要把它放慢
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.60,0:01:32.22,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And once it gets close we want to slow things down
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.60,0:01:32.22,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而一旦它接近了 我们要把运行速度放慢
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.26,0:01:35.90,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,so we can actually observe the destruction in extreme detail.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.26,0:01:35.90,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这样我们就能真正观察到破坏的极端细节
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.44,0:01:39.36,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,The main thing that's going to drive this destruction isn't the impact
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.44,0:01:39.36,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,驱动这种破坏的主要因素不是冲击力
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.36,0:01:42.04,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,because you're not going to have these things impact.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.36,0:01:42.04,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,因为这些东西之间不会有冲击力
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.07,0:01:44.78,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,We've adjusted it to make sure that doesn't happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.07,0:01:44.78,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,我们已经调整了它 以确保这不会发生
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.34,0:01:49.67,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,What is going to happen is the gravitational forces are going to stretch both objects
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.34,0:01:49.67,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,将要发生的是 引力将拉伸两个物体
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.73,0:01:52.40,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and you're going to have extreme tides.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.73,0:01:52.40,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而你将会看到极端的潮汐
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.43,0:01:54.50,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,You're going to have stretching of the bodies.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.43,0:01:54.50,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,你将会看到 天体们会被拉伸
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.93,0:01:58.10,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And that's actually going to cause earthquakes on earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.93,0:01:58.10,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而这实际上将导致地球上的地震
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.47,0:02:03.32,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Massive tidal effects. You're going to have water flows inundating the surface
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.47,0:02:03.32,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,大规模的潮汐效应 你将会看到水流淹没地表
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.83,0:02:08.35,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and of course a whole bunch of other stuff that will really soak up your VFX budget.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.83,0:02:08.35,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,当然还有一大堆其他的东西 那些都将真正耗尽你的视觉特效预算
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.56,0:02:11.68,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,The moon on the other hand it comes off even worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.56,0:02:11.68,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,在另一方面 月球的情况更糟糕
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.68,0:02:15.69,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,It actually gets torn apart as it flies inside the roche limit.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.68,0:02:15.69,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,实际上 当它在洛希极限内飞行时 它被撕碎了
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.11,0:02:21.28,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,It'll have debris pulled off the surface and that stuff will go into different orbits.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.11,0:02:21.28,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它将有碎片被拉出表面 并且这些东西将进入不同的轨道
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.92,0:02:26.27,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Now some of this stuff is actually going to go into an orbit that brings it back to earth
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.92,0:02:26.27,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,那么 这些东西中的一部分 实际上会进入一个会将其带回地球的轨道
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.30,0:02:30.08,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,so if I select the planet earth and we drag this down
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.30,0:02:30.08,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,所以 如果我选择地球 并且我们把这个拖下来
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.08,0:02:32.08,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,so you can see the simulation.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.08,0:02:32.08,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这样你就可以看到模拟的情况
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.08,0:02:33.68,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Oh well let's do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.08,0:02:33.68,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,让我们这样做吧
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.84,0:02:35.26,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Yeah so we can see the simulation.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.84,0:02:35.26,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,是的 所以我们可以看到模拟的情况
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.47,0:02:39.12,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Oh. Yeah we've already had one impact there.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.47,0:02:39.12,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,哦是的 我们这里已经有一个撞击了
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.28,0:02:41.71,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Oh just skimming by past.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.28,0:02:41.71,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,啊啊啊 哦 这个刚刚略过了过去
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.40,0:02:43.76,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,I'm surprised those missed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.40,0:02:43.76,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,我很惊讶 这些都错过了
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.80,0:02:44.82,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,That was a close shave.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.80,0:02:44.82,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这是个很好的例子
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.41,0:02:49.98,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Now at this point everywhere on the planet earth is getting seriously damaged.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.41,0:02:49.98,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,那么 在这时 地球上的所有地方都受到了严重破坏
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.28,0:02:52.48,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Not just from the impacts
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.28,0:02:52.48,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这些破坏不仅仅是来自撞击
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.48,0:02:58.76,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,but just by the fact that we have put so much energy into the system with this close pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.48,0:02:58.76,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而只是因为 我们在这次近距离通过时向地月系 投入了如此多的能量
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.60,0:03:03.21,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,You have to imagine that this kind of gravitational disruption
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.60,0:03:03.21,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,你必须想象 这种引力的扰动
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.53,0:03:07.58,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,will probably move the crust and the mantle around enough that
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.53,0:03:07.58,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,可能会使地壳和地幔发生足够的移动 以至于
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.61,0:03:12.54,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,it will cause a lot of energy that's built up in fault lines to release.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.61,0:03:12.54,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它将导致大量积聚在断层线上的能量释放
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.57,0:03:14.53,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,You'll have earthquakes all over the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.57,0:03:14.53,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,世界各地将发生地震
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.68,0:03:17.59,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,As I said that's the task for the VFX artist.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.68,0:03:17.59,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,正如我所说 这些是视觉特效艺术家的任务
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.50,0:03:19.80,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,So look this is not good.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.50,0:03:19.80,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,所以你看 这不是好事
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.84,0:03:24.78,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,The average temperature on the planet earth is now almost 100 degrees centigrade.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.84,0:03:24.78,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,现在 地球上的平均温度几乎是100摄氏度
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.04,0:03:29.11,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Granted that is largely because there are some very hot areas
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.04,0:03:29.11,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,的确 这主要是因为有一些非常热的地区
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.42,0:03:33.29,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,while the rest of the earth is merely wondering why it's flooded.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.42,0:03:33.29,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,与此同时 地球的其他地方 只是在困惑我们为什么会被淹了
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.23,0:03:38.40,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,The moon on the other hand if we select the moon it's got very hot
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.23,0:03:38.40,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,另一方面 如果我们选中查看月球 它变得非常热
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.40,0:03:44.08,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and the way that is just the simulation had a lot of the stuff that's pulled off it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.40,0:03:44.08,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而这的原因只是 在模拟中 月球上的很多物质被扯掉了
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.17,0:03:47.58,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Has now come back and hit the moon and that sort of raised its temperature
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.17,0:03:47.58,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这些东西现在又回来了 并击中了月球 而这就提高了它的温度
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.60,0:03:52.77,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,along with the energy released by the gravitational interactions the the tidal effects.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.60,0:03:52.77,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,与引力相互作用和潮汐效应释放的能量一起
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.04,0:03:56.31,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Remember the moon Io around Jupiter.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.04,0:03:56.31,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,记得木星周围的卫星艾奥吗
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.31,0:04:01.54,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,It is kept hot by these gravitational interactions with the tides.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.31,0:04:01.54,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这些相互作用引力和潮汐效应释放的能量 使它保持高温
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.18,0:04:05.59,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And in fact it's got so hot now that it is starting to boil
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.18,0:04:05.59,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而事实上 月球现在已经变得如此之热 以至于它开始沸腾了
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.59,0:04:09.69,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and you've got like a cometary tail in this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.59,0:04:09.69,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而在这种情况下 你会有一个像彗星那种的尾巴
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.71,0:04:11.33,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure how accurate that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.71,0:04:11.33,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,我不确定这有多准确
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.76,0:04:14.07,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,But it does bring me to the question of
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.76,0:04:14.07,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但它确实给我带来了这样一个问题
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.08,0:04:21.04,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,how we would actually get 800 meters per second of delta v from the moon or to push the moon around.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.08,0:04:21.04,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,我们如何从月球上获得每秒800米的Dv 或者说用它向周围推动月球
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.38,0:04:26.05,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,So if you think about the best rocket engines we have are the RL-10.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.38,0:04:26.05,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,所以如果你想一下 我们拥有的最好的火箭发动机是RL-10
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.09,0:04:28.08,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,That's a hydrogen oxygen rocket engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.09,0:04:28.08,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,那是一个氢氧火箭发动机
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.66,0:04:33.52,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And it gets about 370 seconds of specific impulse.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.66,0:04:33.52,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而它能创造大约370秒的比冲
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.70,0:04:35.02,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,So if you do the math on that
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.70,0:04:35.02,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,因此 如果你基于它进行计算
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.51,0:04:42.73,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,you would need about one quarter of the moon's mass in propellant to fuel this thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.51,0:04:42.73,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,你将需要质量大约为月球四分之一的推进剂 来为这个东西提供燃料
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.52,0:04:48.60,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And that's a problem because it uses hydrogen and oxygen
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.52,0:04:48.60,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而这是一个问题 因为这个发动机使用的是氢气和氧气
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.20,0:04:57.28,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,so the obvious place to get that hydrogen oxygen is the oceans of the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.20,0:04:57.28,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,所以能获取氢气和氧气的明显地点 是地球上的海洋
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.56,0:05:02.70,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Well the oceans of the earth are about 10% of the mass of the moon.
