Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.60,0:05:12.55,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,you would not have enough propellant to do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.60,0:05:12.55,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,你还是将没有足够的推进剂来做这件事
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.81,0:05:18.35,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,What you really need to do is find some sort of local propellant that is easier and more useful.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.81,0:05:18.35,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而你真正需要做的是 找到某种本地推进剂 这更容易 并且更有用
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.60,0:05:20.74,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,There's not enough water in the moon to do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.60,0:05:20.74,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,月球上没有足够的水来做这件事
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.50,0:05:25.86,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,There is another option is to use a higher more efficient thruster
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.50,0:05:25.86,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,还有一个选择是使用更高效的推进器
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.91,0:05:29.24,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,because one of the problem with chemical thrusters is that
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.91,0:05:29.24,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,因为化学推进器的问题之一是
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.29,0:05:33.29,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,their velocity is comparable to the escape velocity of the moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.29,0:05:33.29,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它们的速度与月球的逃逸速度相当
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.52,0:05:36.11,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,The moon's escape velocity is about two kilometers per second.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.52,0:05:36.11,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,月球的逃逸速度约为每秒两千米
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.14,0:05:40.08,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,That means you lose two kilometers per second off your exhaust velocity
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.14,0:05:40.08,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这意味着你的排气速度每秒减少了两千米
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.13,0:05:42.00,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,because it has to fight against gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.13,0:05:42.00,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,因为它必须与重力作斗争
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.14,0:05:45.68,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,That cuts the performance of your RL-10 in half.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.14,0:05:45.68,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这使你的RL-10的性能减半
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.17,0:05:51.36,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,There's other chemical propulsion systems that you could use that don't use hydrogen and oxygen.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.17,0:05:51.36,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,还有其他化学推进系统你可以使用 它们不使用氢气和氧气
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.36,0:05:57.64,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,There's things like aluminium oxygen where you would take alumina found in the lunar crust
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.36,0:05:57.64,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,有像氧化铝这样的东西 你可以把在月球地壳中找到的氧化铝
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.91,0:06:00.82,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,break it into aluminium and oxygen and use that as a rocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.91,0:06:00.82,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,将其分解成铝和氧 并将其作为火箭燃料使用
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.89,0:06:02.72,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,But that is even lower performance.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.89,0:06:02.72,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但这的性能甚至更低
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.94,0:06:08.56,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,A better idea is something called the magnesium hall effect thruster.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.94,0:06:08.56,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,一个更好的想法 是一个叫做镁燃料霍尔效应推进器的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.60,0:06:11.58,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And this is something that's been investigated I'm not sure it's been built
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.60,0:06:11.58,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,并且这是一个已经被研究过的东西 我不确定它是否已经被制造出来
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.65,0:06:17.75,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,but I know that Busek who make regular hall effect thrusters using xenon and krypton
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.65,0:06:17.75,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但我知道 制造使用氙气和氪气的常规霍尔效应推进器的Busek公司
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.91,0:06:22.17,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,they've demonstrated or they've talked about this with magnesium
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.91,0:06:22.17,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,他们已经证明了 或者说他们已经谈到了使用镁的这个问题
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.19,0:06:25.49,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,you can get specific impulse of about 4000 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.19,0:06:25.49,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,你可以用它得到大约4000秒的比冲力
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.51,0:06:28.80,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,That means the exhaust velocity is 40 kilometers per second
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.51,0:06:28.80,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这意味着排气的速度为每秒40千米
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.80,0:06:34.54,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,so losing two kilometers from the moon's gravity isn't such a big deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.80,0:06:34.54,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,所以 由于月球的重力从中损失两公里并不是什么大问题
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.28,0:06:37.39,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And with that very high performance
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.28,0:06:37.39,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而且 在这种非常高的性能下
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.42,0:06:42.10,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,you would only need about two percent of the mass of the moon to do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.42,0:06:42.10,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,你只需要大约百分之二月球质量的推进剂就可以做到这一点
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.67,0:06:45.57,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,So the next question is is there enough magnesium on the moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.67,0:06:45.57,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,因此 下一个问题是月球上是否有足够的镁
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.62,0:06:48.68,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And looking at the geology from the surface and analysis
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.62,0:06:48.68,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而观察月球表面的地质情况 并分析来看
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.78,0:06:51.61,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,it does seem that there's probably enough oxygen in the moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.78,0:06:51.61,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,看来 月球上是可能有足够的氧
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.68,0:06:55.52,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,On the other hand you would probably have to mine most of the moon
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.68,0:06:55.52,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,在另一方面 你可能必须开采大部分的月球
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.52,0:06:59.09,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,to actually access it to extract out the small part that is magnesium.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.52,0:06:59.09,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,才能真正开采出那一小部分的镁
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.59,0:07:02.80,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,On the other hand if you could make a thruster that worked with pure oxygen
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.59,0:07:02.80,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而在另一方面 如果你能制造一个能用纯氧工作的推进器
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.80,0:07:04.82,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,an ion thruster that would be great
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.80,0:07:04.82,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,也就是一台离子推进器 那就太好了
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.86,0:07:08.34,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,because oxygen is one of the biggest components of the moon by weight.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.86,0:07:08.34,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,因为按重量来说 氧是月球质量上最大的组成部分之一
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.90,0:07:12.47,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,On the other hand trying to run an engine using ionized oxygen
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.90,0:07:12.47,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而在另一方面 试图用离子化的氧气驱动发动机
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.47,0:07:15.12,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,is just asking for engine rich exhaust.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.47,0:07:15.12,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,会使发动机的排气量巨大
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.66,0:07:17.51,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Well the point is it's not going to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.66,0:07:17.51,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但重点是 这些是不可能发生的
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.61,0:07:19.75,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,but of course in the movie they need it to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.61,0:07:19.75,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但当然 在电影中他们需要它发生
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.75,0:07:20.72,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,What do they do.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.75,0:07:20.72,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,他们是怎么做的
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.72,0:07:26.56,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,They use aliens and aliens are a completely possible way to cause the moon to fall to earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.72,0:07:26.56,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,他们利用外星人 而外星人是导致月球落到地球上的一个完全合理的方法
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.78,0:07:28.61,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,They don't need to obey the laws of physics.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.78,0:07:28.61,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,他们不需要遵守物理学定律
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.66,0:07:33.68,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,In fact if I had looked at this trailer and been asked to rate on realism
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.66,0:07:33.68,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,事实上 如果我看了这个预告片 并被要求对现实性进行评分的话
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.90,0:07:38.97,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,I would have said the most unrealistic thing was having the Space Shuttle flying in 2022.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.90,0:07:38.97,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,我会说最不现实的事情是 让航天飞机在2022年飞行
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.00,0:07:43.74,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Now I've been working on the basis that it took 800 meters per second of delta v
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.00,0:07:43.74,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,那么 我上述讨论的基础是 它需要每秒800米的Dv
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.76,0:07:46.82,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,but it turns out that because the moon is so far away
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.76,0:07:46.82,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但事实证明 由于月球离我们如此之远
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.88,0:07:49.74,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,we can use something called a bi-elliptic transfer.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.88,0:07:49.74,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,我们可以使用一种叫做双椭圆转移轨道的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.77,0:07:53.20,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,That is a clever little exploit in the laws of physics.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.77,0:07:53.20,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这是在物理学规律中 一个聪明的小开发
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.23,0:07:56.86,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,That helps us get a little more bang for our buck
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.23,0:07:56.86,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这有助于我们获得更多的收益
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.90,0:07:58.87,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,if we're prepared to take a bit more time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.90,0:07:58.87,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,如果我们准备多花一点时间的话
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.08,0:08:02.21,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,So this is just the earth and the moon so I can demonstrate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.08,0:08:02.21,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,所以这只是地球和月球 所以我可以演示一下
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.73,0:08:08.11,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,What we're going to do instead is boost it up to a very highly eccentric orbit
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.73,0:08:08.11,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,我们要做的是把它提升到一个高度偏心的轨道上
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.13,0:08:09.38,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,a long way from the earth
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.13,0:08:09.38,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,在离地球很远的地方
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.66,0:08:13.98,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and then we'll slow it down and it turns out this needs less delta v
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.66,0:08:13.98,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,然后我们把它放慢 结果发现这需要更少的Dv
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.02,0:08:19.63,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,so if I take this we're going to push the semi-major axis and the pericenter distance out as far as we can
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.02,0:08:19.63,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,所以如果我用这种方式 我们要把半长轴和近心点的距离尽可能地推远一些
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.31,0:08:23.98,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,so that it's moving very very slowly.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.31,0:08:23.98,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这样 它就会非常非常缓慢地移动
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.47,0:08:27.42,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And the most this will take us is about 400 meters per second.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.47,0:08:27.42,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而这最多需要每秒400米左右的Dv
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.48,0:08:30.55,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Now look I've pushed the apocenter distance to undefined.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.48,0:08:30.55,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,现在看 我已经把远心点距离推到了未定义
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.58,0:08:36.95,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,That means it's now on uh on an orbit which is parabolic or hyperbolic.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.58,0:08:36.95,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这意味着它现在在一个抛物线或双曲线的轨道上
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.99,0:08:38.24,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,It will never come back to earth
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.99,0:08:38.24,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它将永远不会回到地球上来
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.24,0:08:40.28,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,because it's exceeded escape velocity.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.24,0:08:40.28,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,因为它已经超过了逃逸速度
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.45,0:08:42.32,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,So I need to slow this down just a bit
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.45,0:08:42.32,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,所以我需要把这个速度放慢一点
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.32,0:08:45.57,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,until we get the apocenter to be redefined
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.32,0:08:45.57,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,直到我们得到重新定义的远地点
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.40,0:08:49.27,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and you'll notice the semi-major axis is negative in this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.40,0:08:49.27,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而你会注意到 半长轴在这里是负的
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.27,0:08:53.12,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,This is just a consequence of the mathematics modeling these conic sections.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.27,0:08:53.12,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这只是为这些圆锥截面数学建模的结果
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.29,0:08:53.83,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,There we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.29,0:08:53.83,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,好了
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.07,0:08:58.72,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,That is an extremely highly eccentric orbit that goes out to 0.45 au.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.07,0:08:58.72,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这是一个极其高度偏心的轨道 其一直延伸到0.45天文单位
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.30,0:09:02.74,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,It's going to take years to get there in this simulation
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.30,0:09:02.74,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,在这个模拟中 要花数年时间才能变成这样
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.44,0:09:07.85,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,but the good news is that we only spent 400 meters per second to do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.44,0:09:07.85,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但好消息是 我们只花了每秒400米的Dv来做到这个
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.64,0:09:11.70,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Okay so here we are about 30 years later
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.64,0:09:11.70,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,好了 所以我们到了 大约30年后
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.16,0:09:15.36,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and the moon because we've pushed it out on this orbit
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.16,0:09:15.36,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而月球 因为我们把它推到了这个轨道上
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.36,0:09:18.41,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,it's moving at only 8.4 meters per second
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.36,0:09:18.41,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它的移动速度只有每秒8.4米
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.46,0:09:21.68,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,so it takes a tiny amount of velocity
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.46,0:09:21.68,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,所以它需要一个很小的速度
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.96,0:09:26.46,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,to slow it down enough that it will now pass very close to or hit the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.96,0:09:26.46,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,来使它足够慢下来 使它现在会非常接近或撞击地球
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.88,0:09:30.32,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And it only took about 400 meters per second to push it up here
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.88,0:09:30.32,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而我们只用了每秒400米的Dv就把它推到了这里
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.37,0:09:34.52,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,so there's a sort of basic rule if you can do like a bi-elliptic transfer
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.37,0:09:34.52,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,所以这里有一种基本的规则 如果你能进行像双椭圆轨道的转移
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.92,0:09:40.95,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,then the minimum delta v to reach any target is the escape velocity, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.92,0:09:40.95,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,那么到达任何目标的最小Dv 就是逃逸速度 对吗
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.97,0:09:43.81,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Because that's your sort of the limit on this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.97,0:09:43.81,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,因为那是你在这方面的极限
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.26,0:09:50.01,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,So yeah if I want to bring the pericenter distance down to the surface of the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.26,0:09:50.01,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,所以是的 如果我想把近心点的距离降低到地球表面
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.32,0:09:51.60,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Doesn't take very long.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.32,0:09:51.60,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这并不需要很长的时间
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.63,0:09:53.39,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,It takes a few meters per second.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.63,0:09:53.39,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,每秒只需要几米
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.69,0:09:59.68,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Now this only works when we've got the earth and the moon
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.69,0:09:59.68,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,那么 这只在我们只有地球和月球的情况下有效
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.68,0:10:03.22,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,because if we try to push something up to this highly eccentric orbit
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.68,0:10:03.22,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,因为如果我们试图把东西推到这个高度偏心的轨道上
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.68,0:10:09.76,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,as it's out so far away from the earth it won't escape the earth's gravity
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.68,0:10:09.76,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,因为它离地球太远了 虽然它将无法逃脱地球的引力
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.98,0:10:13.72,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,but other planets influence will become more important than the earth
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.98,0:10:13.72,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但其他行星的影响将变得比地球的影响更为重要
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.15,0:10:18.45,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and they will pull it off in its own weird directions.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.15,0:10:18.45,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而且它们会把这个东西 拉到它自己的奇怪方向上
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.77,0:10:21.76,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Now that doesn't mean we can't make the moon hit the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.77,0:10:21.76,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,那么 这并不意味着我们不能让月球撞击地球
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.76,0:10:25.12,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,It just means that we can't use this very simple formulation.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.76,0:10:25.12,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它只是意味着我们不能使用这个非常简单的公式
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.60,0:10:30.74,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,It's going to take a lot more cout math and a lot more calculus and simulation
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.60,0:10:30.74,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这将需要更多的数学计算 更多的微积分和更多的模拟
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.04,0:10:35.60,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,to bring the object into an orbit where we know that we'll hit the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.04,0:10:35.60,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,来把这个物体带入一个我们知道它会撞击地球的轨道
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.66,0:10:37.72,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,So here it's coming back down now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.66,0:10:37.72,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,所以在这里 它现在又下来了
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.06,0:10:38.84,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And I have to be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.06,0:10:38.84,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而我必须要小心
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.90,0:10:40.77,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,I don't make this happen too fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.90,0:10:40.77,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,我不会让这一切发生得太快
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.80,0:10:43.34,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,The orbital period is 60 odd years
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.80,0:10:43.34,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,轨道周期是60年左右
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.68,0:10:45.82,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,because you've got earth type gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.68,0:10:45.82,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,因为你有地球类型的引力
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.00,0:10:47.77,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Whoa and there we slung by.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.00,0:10:47.77,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,哇 它在那里滑过去了
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.79,0:10:48.80,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,You see I messed it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.79,0:10:48.80,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,你看 我把它搞乱了
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.22,0:10:51.27,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,But this is a simulation so I can rewind
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.22,0:10:51.27,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但这是一个模拟 所以我可以回放
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.27,0:10:54.54,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and we can watch the moon get torn apart again if that's your thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.27,0:10:54.54,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,我们可以再看一次月球被撕碎 如果你喜欢的话
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.94,0:10:57.56,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Now this isn't hollywood VFX quality.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.94,0:10:57.56,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,那么 这不是好莱坞的视觉特效质量
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.61,0:11:00.87,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,In fact the fidelity of the simulation is missing a lot of stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.61,0:11:00.87,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,事实上 模拟的逼真度缺少很多东西
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.90,0:11:03.82,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Everything is still treated as point masses more or less.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.90,0:11:03.82,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,所有东西都或多或少仍被视为点状质量
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.34,0:11:08.30,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,There is a type of simulation called smoothed particle hydrodynamics
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.34,0:11:08.30,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,有一种叫做平滑粒子流体力学的模拟方法
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.32,0:11:12.07,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,which is basically a way of modeling fluidized bodies
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.32,0:11:12.07,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,那基本上是一种对流化体进行建模的方法
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.07,0:11:15.27,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,under self-gravity and close gravitational interaction
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.07,0:11:15.27,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,根据自重和密切的引力相互作用
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.33,0:11:18.37,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,so the earth can be treated as a fluid.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.33,0:11:18.37,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,因此 地球可以被看作是一种流体
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.38,0:11:23.02,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,I mean after all most of it is more or less liquid rock under the right conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.38,0:11:23.02,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,我的意思是 毕竟在适当的条件下 它的大部分或多或少都是液体岩石
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.36,0:11:25.60,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And one of the developers of universe sandbox
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.36,0:11:25.60,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而宇宙沙盒的一个开发者
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.60,0:11:30.11,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,did smooth particle hydrodynamics simulations for his postgraduate work.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.60,0:11:30.11,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,在他的研究生工作中做了流畅的粒子流体力学模拟
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.56,0:11:37.21,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And about 18 months ago the devs of universe sandbox showed off some smooth particle codes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.56,0:11:37.21,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,并且在大约18个月前 宇宙沙盒的开发者展示了一些光滑粒子代码
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.66,0:11:40.95,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,They weren't properly integrated it with the rest of the system.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.66,0:11:40.95,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,他们并没有将其与系统的其他部分适当地整合
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.95,0:11:42.26,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,I would love to see that
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.95,0:11:42.26,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,我很想看到这一点
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.29,0:11:47.83,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,because I would love to be able to crash the planets together with greater fidelity and detail
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.29,0:11:47.83,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,因为我希望能够以更高的逼真度和细节 将行星撞在一起
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.87,0:11:48.86,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and frankly
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.87,0:11:48.86,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,并且坦率地说
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.68,0:11:55.59,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,I'm looking forward to that being in universe sandbox more than I'm looking forward to a movie called moonfall.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.68,0:11:55.59,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,比起电影《月球坠落》 我更期待这项功能在宇宙沙盒中的出现
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.00,0:11:58.45,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,I'm Scott Manley. Fly safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.00,0:11:58.45,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,我是Scott Manley 切记 注意飞行安全
